text: Rathanadav, also called Carron Henge, Rathnadob, Rathnadov or Fort Aengus (after Óengus mac Nad Froích),http://www.tii.ie/tii- library/archaeology/Brochures%20and%20Posters/N8-Cashel-Bypass-and-N74-Link- Road-historic-POSTER.pdf is a ringfort (rath) and henge, and a National Monument located in County Tipperary, Ireland. ==Location== Rathanadav is located on a hill about south of Cashel, east of the River Suir. It may be part of the larger Rathnadrinna royal complex, located to the north. ==Description== Rathanadav is a rath enclosed by a wide henge about in diameter, with an entrance near the north. Inside are five low mounds which may contain burials or maybe the remains of internal structures. ==References== Category:Archaeological sites in County Tipperary Category:National Monuments in County Tipperary
title: Rathanadav
